UPDATE Cities 
SET description = "<strong>'Welcome to Mumbai</strong>, famously dubbed the <strong>'City of Dreams'</strong> and India's relentless <strong>financial powerhouse</strong>. Evolving from a humble archipelago of <strong>seven islands</strong> originally inhabited by <strong>Koli fishermen</strong>, its history is deeply shaped by layers of Portuguese and British colonial influence. Today, the metropolis is globally celebrated as the dazzling epicenter of <strong>Bollywood</strong> and home to iconic architectural marvels like the <strong>Gateway of India</strong>. The cultural fabric here is a vibrant, resilient melting pot, reaching its zenith during the spectacular, city-wide festivities of <strong>Ganesh Chaturthi</strong>. For gastronomes, Mumbai's legendary street food scene offers an explosion of flavors, spearheaded by the iconic, spicy <strong>Vada Pav</strong> and the richly buttery <strong>Pav Bhaji</strong>. Sports run profoundly through the city's veins, with <strong>cricket</strong> treated as an absolute religion and the historic <strong>Wankhede Stadium</strong> serving as its ultimate temple. Whether strolling down the sweeping Queen's Necklace of <strong>Marine Drive</strong> or navigating the bustling local trains, the city's energetic pulse is instantly infectious. Beautifully chaotic and endlessly inspiring, Mumbai offers a uniquely welcoming spirit that seamlessly bridges its historical heritage with a soaring, modern ambition.<strong>'</strong>"
WHERE name = 'Mumbai';

UPDATE Cities 
SET description = "<strong>'Welcome to Hyderabad</strong>, widely celebrated as the <strong>'City of Pearls'</strong> and a booming global hub for <strong>information technology</strong>. Founded in <strong>1591</strong> by <strong>Muhammad Quli Qutb Shah</strong>, the city boasts a regal history steeped in the rich legacy of the <strong>Nizams</strong> and stunning Indo-Islamic architecture. It is most famous worldwide for the iconic <strong>Charminar</strong>, a magnificent 16th-century monument with four grand minarets that stands as the city's enduring historical symbol. The local culture is a beautiful synthesis of North and South Indian traditions, famously characterized by its warm, polite traditional etiquette known as <strong>'Tehzeeb'</strong>. For culinary enthusiasts, the city offers an unforgettable gastronomic journey, headlined by the rich, slow-cooked perfection of authentic <strong>Hyderabadi Biryani</strong>. This royal cuisine is perfectly complemented by beloved local delicacies like savory Haleem and the traditional apricot dessert, <strong>Qubani ka Meetha</strong>. Sports play a vital role in the city's energetic rhythm, with cricket commanding massive devotion alongside a soaring, world-class badminton culture. Seamlessly blending ancient monuments with the cutting-edge skyline of <strong>HITEC City</strong>, Hyderabad offers a vibrant experience that honors its royal past while embracing a dynamic future.<strong>'</strong>"
WHERE name = 'Hyderabad';

UPDATE Cities 
SET description = "<strong>'Welcome to Bhubaneswar</strong>, proudly hailed as the <strong>'Temple City of India'</strong> and the thriving <strong>capital of Odisha</strong>. With a profound history tracing back over two millennia, it served as the ancient capital of the <strong>Kalinga empire</strong> and showcases a unique, historical confluence of Hindu, Buddhist, and Jain heritage. The city is globally renowned for its majestic Kalinga architecture, most strikingly embodied by the towering 11th-century <strong>Lingaraj Temple</strong> and the intricate, rock-cut <strong>Udayagiri</strong> and <strong>Khandagiri caves</strong>. Culturally, it is a vibrant epicenter where the graceful classical <strong>Odissi</strong> dance and meticulous <strong>Pattachitra</strong> scroll paintings continue to flourish alongside rapid urban growth. Culinary explorers are treated to authentic Odia gastronomy, featuring wholesome, flavorful staples like <strong>Dalma</strong> alongside legendary, caramelized sweets such as <strong>Chhena Poda</strong> and <strong>Pahala Rasagola</strong>. In recent years, Bhubaneswar has spectacularly transformed into the undisputed <strong>'Sports Capital of India'</strong>, anchored by the world-class <strong>Kalinga Stadium</strong> which regularly hosts prestigious global tournaments like the <strong>Men's FIH Hockey World Cup</strong>. Beyond its ancient roots and athletic prowess, it has rapidly emerged as a premier educational and IT hub, attracting top talent from across the nation. Seamlessly intertwining divine antiquity with dynamic, modern infrastructure, Bhubaneswar offers an incredibly enriching experience that captivates historians, sports fans, and professionals alike.<strong>'</strong>"
WHERE name = 'Bhubaneswar';

UPDATE Cities 
