SET description = "<strong>'Welcome to Kolkata</strong>, universally cherished as the <strong>'City of Joy'</strong> and India's undisputed <strong>intellectual and cultural capital</strong>. Serving as the capital of British India until <strong>1911</strong>, its grand history is visibly etched into stunning colonial-era architecture like the magnificent <strong>Victoria Memorial</strong> and the iconic, cantilevered <strong>Howrah Bridge</strong>. It is globally famous for its profound literary and artistic heritage, proudly claiming Nobel laureates like <strong>Rabindranath Tagore</strong> and maintaining an unmatched, daily passion for cinema, poetry, and theater. The city's cultural heartbeat reaches a spectacular crescendo during <strong>Durga Puja</strong>, a massive, vibrant festival that seamlessly transforms the streets into an immersive public art gallery. Gastronomy in Kolkata is deeply emotional and distinct, revolving around a fierce love for mustard-infused river fish and world-renowned Bengali confectionery. Staples like the slow-cooked, aromatic <strong>Kosha Mangsho</strong>, delicate <strong>Macher Jhol</strong>, and iconic desserts like Rasgulla and Sandesh are absolute culinary imperatives. Sports are treated with fanatical devotion, with the colossal <strong>Salt Lake Stadium</strong> serving as the historic epicenter of <strong>Indian football</strong>, alongside a massive, enduring love for cricket at the legendary <strong>Eden Gardens</strong>. Beautifully balancing its faded colonial grandeur with a fiercely passionate modern intellect, Kolkata remains a profoundly soulful metropolis that thrives on art, lively conversation, and an indomitable spirit.<strong>'</strong>"
